Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • Model.User
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class User
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is the User class which has the constructors for creating a user. It also checks whether the user is an admin or not. It has basic setters and getters
    Version:
    0.4 19/5/22
    Author:
    Chris, Martin, Levente, Kruno
    See Also:

        public User​(int age,
            java.lang.String username,
            java.lang.String password,
            boolean isAdmin,
            java.lang.String email,
            java.lang.String address,
            java.lang.String name,
            java.time.LocalDate bday,
            boolean hasSubscription,
            int balance,
            java.lang.String salt)
        A ten argument constructor taking in every attribute
        Parameters:
        age - Age in user
        username - The username used to log-in
        password - The password needed to log-in
        isAdmin - Shows whether the user has administrator priveledges
        email - The e-mail to contact the user if needed
        address - The physical mailing address to use to send the games
        name - The full name of the user
        bday - The date of birth of the user
        hasSubscription - Shows whether the user has an active subscription and can rent games
        balance - The balance of money that the user has
        salt - salt used for password encryption
